		<div class="story-heads">
		<h1>Sigrid Nunez, Julie Buntin, Pamela Colloff, and more: 20 new books out today!</h1>
			</div>
	</div>
										<div class="byline-date">
					<span class="byline"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/juliahass/"  title="Julia Hass">Julia Hass</a></span>
					<span class="hr"></span>
					<span class="date">July 14, 2026</span>
				</div>
						<div class="story-body">
								<p style="text-align: left;">The July fiction continues: Julie Buntin&#8217;s much anticipated follow-up to <em>Marlena</em> is out today, Sigrid Nunez&#8217;s new collection drops, along with Jem Calder&#8217;s <em>I Want You To Be Happy</em>. There&#8217;s a multitude of nonfiction as well, such as Pamela Colloff&#8217;s true crime investigation and Lucy Schiller&#8217;s deep-dive into aging in America. Have a great reading week!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264644" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/sigrid-nunez-it-will-come-back-to-you-the-collected-stories/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Sigrid Nunez, It Will Come Back to You- The Collected Stories" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories-678x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264644" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories-199x300.jpg" alt="Sigrid Nunez, It Will Come Back to You: The Collected Stories" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories.jpg 993w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sigrid Nunez, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9798217179152" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>It Will Come Back to You: The Collected Stories</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Riverhead)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Nunez injects these stories with a deep tenderness and a wry sense of humor, all the while challenging our conceptions of what it means to live an ordinary life.”<br />
<em>–Harpers Bazaar</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="273164" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026-part-two/attachment/243039897/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1684,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="julie buntin famous men" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-674x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-273164" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-197x300.jpg" alt="julie buntin famous men" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-1011x1536.jpg 1011w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-1347x2048.jpg 1347w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/243039897-scaled.jpg 1684w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Julie Buntin, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593229958" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Famous Men</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Random House)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Haunting and knife-bright<i>, Famous Men</i> renders womanhood with unsettling clarity and reckons with the absolute ache of becoming.”<br />
<em>–</em>Kiley Reid</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="274066" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/ten-great-nonfiction-titles-to-read-in-july/catch-the-devil/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/catch-the-devil.png" data-orig-size="514,774" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="catch the devil" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/catch-the-devil.png" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-274066" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/catch-the-devil-199x300.png" alt="catch the devil" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/catch-the-devil-199x300.png 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/catch-the-devil-40x60.png 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/catch-the-devil-33x50.png 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/catch-the-devil.png 514w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Pamela Colloff, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593230862" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Catch the Devil: A True Story of Murder, Deception, and Injustice on the Gulf Coast</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Knopf)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“Incendiary, emotionally devastating. [This] is a feat of dogged reporting, bravura storytelling, and clear-eyed moral conscience.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Patrick Radden Keefe</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="273545" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/?attachment_id=273545" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1669,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="i want you to be happy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-668x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-273545" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-196x300.jpg" alt="i want you to be happy" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-1335x2048.jpg 1335w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/i-want-you-to-be-happy-scaled.jpg 1669w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Jem Calder, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780374620554" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>I Want You to be Happy</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(FSG)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;An irresistible novel that asks complex questions about contemporary life and refuses easy answers. I couldn&#8217;t stop reading.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Sally Rooney</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="274092" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/sigrid-nunez-julie-buntin-pamela-colloff-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2125" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Renoir Girls, Catherine Ostler" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-675x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-274092" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-198x300.jpg" alt="The Renoir Girls, Catherine Ostler" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-675x1024.jpg 675w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-768x1166.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-1012x1536.jpg 1012w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-1349x2048.jpg 1349w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/the-renoir-girls-9781668232484_hr.jpg 1400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Catherine Ostler, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781668232484" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Renoir Girls: A Hidden History of Art, War &amp; Betrayal</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Atria)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“Profoundly moving &#8230; With consummate skill and impressive research, Ostler tells the story.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Daily Mail</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="274101" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/sigrid-nunez-julie-buntin-pamela-colloff-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/81njbuefqjl-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/81NjBUefQJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="669,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Cloudthief, Nathaniel Rich" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/81NjBUefQJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-274101" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/81NjBUefQJL._UF10001000_QL80_-201x300.jpg" alt="Cloudthief, Nathaniel Rich" width="201" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/81NjBUefQJL._UF10001000_QL80_-201x300.jpg 201w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/81NjBUefQJL._UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/81NjBUefQJL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/81NjBUefQJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 669w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 201px) 100vw, 201px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nathaniel Rich, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780374619794" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Cloudthief</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(MCD)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;[A] rambunctious, thoroughly entertaining heist novel.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Harpers</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="274100" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/sigrid-nunez-julie-buntin-pamela-colloff-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/816jhnp9gal-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/816jhnp9gAL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Aging Out, Lucy Schiller" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/816jhnp9gAL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-274100" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/816jhnp9gAL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" alt="Aging Out, Lucy Schiller" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/816jhnp9gAL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/816jhnp9gAL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/816jhnp9gAL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/816jhnp9gAL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 658w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lucy Schiller, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781250344526" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Aging Out: An Exploration of Caregiving, Community, and How Americans Grow Old</em></a></strong><br />
